claude
______

# Ode to Disco

There once was a dance called disco,
Where folks moved like wild San Francisco.
    With lights flashing bright,
    Through the glittering night,
And pants that were tight as Crisco!

A DJ would spin funky beats,
While dancers showed off flashy feats.
    In platform shoes high,
    They'd reach for the sky,
As the Bee Gees sang falsetto treats.

The seventies came and then went,
But disco's divine testament
    Lives on in our hearts,
    When the music restarts,
And the mirror ball spins heaven-sent!

